SANEPIC - Signal And Noise Estimation Procedure Including Correlation
=====================================================================

This is Sanepic, a bolometer arrays data reduction algorithm implemented in C/C++.

Sanepic is a free, public software, you can redistribute it and/or modify it under
the terms of General Public License.

The GNU General Public License does not permit this software to be
redistributed in proprietary programs.

This project is distributed in the hope that it will be useful, but
WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

Availability
============

The current stable version of Sanepic is always available from 

http://www.ias.u-psud.fr/sanepic/

in the download "section"


Installation
============

Sanepic follows the standard GNU installation procedure (automake/autoconf).  Please consult
the INSTALL file in this distribution for more detailed instructions.

For information about specific platforms and compilers see the
"Compilation Notes" section in the INSTALL file.

More information about Sanepic
==========================

The project homepage is http://www.ias.u-psud.fr/sanepic/

The Sanepic user Manual is accessible from IAS wiki at the address below : 

http://www.ias.u-psud.fr/wiki/tiki-index.php?page=SpirePhotSanepic&structure=Herschel

User guide is in English only. No translation in other language is planned.

Reporting Bugs
==============

Details of compilation problems can be found in the INSTALL file.

If you find a bug, please report it using the "support" section in 

http://www.ias.u-psud.fr/sanepic/

All bug reports should include:

       The hardware and operating system
       The compiler used, including version number and compilation options
       A description of the bug behaviour

Any errors or omissions in the manual can also be reported to the
same address.


